{"scenario": "XMEM-03:B", "turn_index": 0, "variant": "recommend a moisturizer", "request": {"message": "recommend a moisturizer", "conversation_id": "46378c24-d3fa-4e41-b7ab-05a8a5f3f994"}, "response_body": {"response": "for oily skin, you want a lightweight moisturizer with ceramides + panthenol that won't clog you. ceramides lock in hydration and repair barrier; panthenol soothes and reduces redness. skip heavy creams or occlusives in the AM. use the moisturizer after your active (azelaic or niacinamide) and before SPF. specific product rec depends on what's available to you. look for a gel-cream or lightweight lotion labeled \"non-comedogenic\" with ceramides listed in the first 5 ingredients. apply to damp skin right after your active for better absorption.", "choices": [], "multi_choice": false, "input_widget": null, "progress": null, "products": [{"name": "The Ordinary Azelaic Acid Suspension 10%", "brand": "The Ordinary", "url": "https://www.amazon.com/The-Ordinary-Azelaic-Acid-Suspension-10-Percent/dp/B0DNN8Z1PD", "description": "Azelaic acid for redness, PIH, and mild rosacea \u2014 pregnancy-safe.", "image": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/P/B0DNN8Z1PD.jpg"}, {"name": "The Ordinary Niacinamide 10% + Zinc 1%", "brand": "The Ordinary", "url": "https://www.amazon.com/The-Ordinary-Niacinamide-10-Percent-+-Zinc-1-Percent/dp/B06VSX2B1S", "description": "10% niacinamide for sebum control and pore appearance.", "image": ""}, {"name": "CeraVe PM Facial Moisturizing Lotion", "brand": "CeraVe", "url": "https://www.amazon.com/Cerave-PM-Facial-Moisturizing-Lotion/dp/B00365DABC", "description": "Lightweight ceramide + niacinamide moisturizer for nightly use.", "image": "https://m.media-amazon.com/images/P/B00365DABC.jpg"}], "created_at": "2026-07-05T19:19:56.804629", "conversation_id": "46378c24-d3fa-4e41-b7ab-05a8a5f3f994", "confirm": null, "visual_blocks": [], "method_metadata": null}, "status_code": 200, "latency_s": 7.02, "transport_error": null, "checks": [{"na